From the Infowars web site ::

On this, the Thursday edition of the Alex Jones Show, Mike Adams of Natural News sits in for Alex. 

Mike talks with Julie Bass, the Michigan woman facing jail time for the crime of planting a vegetable garden. 

Mike also talks with Jeffrey M. Smith, author of the number one GMO bestseller Seeds of Deception and Genetic Roulette, both available at the Infowars store. 

Jonathan W. Emord, a former attorney with the Federal Communications Commission who now practices constitutional and administrative law, also talks with Mike Adams. 

journalist and researcher Aaron Dykes and Prison Planet.com journalist and editor Paul Joseph Watson also make appearances on today's show.
